Haven't been able to do much except read this stuff for awhile.  The id idea seems worthwhile, so I'll do a quick bio.<br><br>
Joined the Crotch in 1967, boot camp at MCRD San Diego (&quot;Hollywood Marines&quot;, to you PI types).  Radio school then on to 3rd battalion, 1st marines, 1st marine division, mostly around DaNang.  Lot's of booby traps, lots of sand, the occasional odd ambush, etc.  Got back to the World just as the artronauts were landing on the moon.  Finished out my enlistment at Santa Ana Helicopter Station, then started school at University of New Mexico, Jan. 1970.  That May was Kent State and Jackson State, and the campus went nuts.  What a head trip!  I've gone on with my life since then, but there isn't a day that passes that I don't think about 'Nam.
